        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What is Haystack?"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Haystack (by deepset) is an open-source Python framework for building production search and RAG pipelines. Unlike LangChain's chain metaphor or LlamaIndex's index-centric model, Haystack structures everything as a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Pipeline",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2014 a directed acyclic graph (DAG) of typed "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Components",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". Each component declares its input and output sockets; the pipeline routes data between them."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Pipeline:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " a DAG of connected components; runs synchronously, passing typed dicts between nodes"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Component:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " any Python class decorated with "
                  },
